From: moleksy <maciej.oleksy@intel.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix: disable DPDK --remap-lcore-ids for MTL multi-process lcore control

--remap-lcore-ids causes lcore ID collisions in the global MtlManager
table when multiple MTL processes run with disjoint CPU sets, because
all processes remap to the same 0..N ID space.

Apply against MTL commit c02b9f6e3169d213bc2130f5459b6c1176e5e2e7 (v26.01.0.DEV).

---
 lib/src/dev/mt_dev.c | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/src/dev/mt_dev.c b/lib/src/dev/mt_dev.c
index a516a165..43d57e29 100644
--- a/lib/src/dev/mt_dev.c
+++ b/lib/src/dev/mt_dev.c
@@ -426,8 +426,11 @@ static int dev_eal_init(struct mtl_init_params* p, struct mt_kport_info* kport_i
       argc++;
   }
 
-#if RTE_VERSION >= RTE_VERSION_NUM(25, 11, 0, 0)
-  argv[argc] = "--remap-lcore-ids"; /* --remap-lcore-ids */
+  /* NOTE: --remap-lcore-ids removed — it causes lcore ID collisions in the
+   * global MtlManager table when multiple MTL processes run with disjoint
+   * CPU sets, because all processes remap to the same 0..N ID space. */
+#if 0 /* was: RTE_VERSION >= RTE_VERSION_NUM(25, 11, 0, 0) */
+  argv[argc] = "--remap-lcore-ids";
   argc++;
 #endif
 
-- 
2.43.0
